      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Melt 10g<span class=\"text-purple\"> [15g] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[20g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> in a pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add 10g <span class=\"text-purple\">[15g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[20g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> into the roux, a little at a time, and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains – this is your <strong>béchamel sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
